text: Haskerdijken () is a small village in Heerenveen in the province of Friesland, the Netherlands. It had a population of around 395 in January 2017.Kerncijfers wijken en buurten 2017 - CBS Statline ==History== Before 2014, Haskerdijken was part of the Skarsterlân municipality and before 1984 it was part of Haskerland. ==References== ==External links== Category:Populated places in Friesland
title: Haskerdijken
